            "value": "%3Cp%3EThe%20King%20James%20Version%20of%20this%20verse%20says%20Abraham%20was%20%22fully%20persuaded%22%20(v.%2021).%20When%20you%20are%20dealing%20with%20something%20as%20impossible%20as%20having%20a%20child%20at%20the%20age%20of%20one%20hundred%2C%20your%20faith%20must%20be%20rock-solid!%20Abraham%20faced%20the%20fact%20that%20his%20body%20was%20dead%20(Romans%204%3A19)%2C%20but%20he%20did%20not%20allow%20that%20consideration%20to%20weaken%20his%20faith.%20He%20came%20to%20a%20point%20in%20which%20his%20beliefs%20did%20not%20waver%20and%20he%20was%20%22fully%20persuaded.%22%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EWhen%20confronted%20with%20an%20impossibility%2C%20you%20must%20face%20the%20facts%20with%20the%20truth%2C%20which%20is%20embodied%20in%20the%20promises%20of%20God.%20As%20you%20spend%20time%20meditating%20on%20the%20promises%20of%20God%2C%20you%20will%20become%20%22fully%20persuaded.%22%20His%20promises%20will%20so%20saturate%20your%20mind%20and%20thinking%20that%20you%20will%20no%20longer%20waver%20in%20doubt%20when%20looking%20at%20outward%20circumstances.%20Rather%2C%20your%20heart%20will%20be%20convinced%20and%20remain%20fixed%2C%20regardless%20of%20what%20your%20mind%20thinks.%20Your%20heart%20will%20overflow%20with%20a%20faith%20that%20knows%20God%20has%20the%20power%20to%20do%20what%20He%20has%20promised.%20At%20that%20point%2C%20nothing%20the%20devil%20can%20do%20or%20say%20will%20move%20you%20from%20your%20position%20of%20faith.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EKeep%20reading%2C%20studying%2C%20and%20digging%20into%20God's%20promises.%20Persist%20in%20tearing%20down%20any%20area%20of%20unbelief%2C%20until%20you%20are%20%22fully%20persuaded.%22%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
