            "value": "%3Cdiv%20class%3D%22%20NLT%20NLT%20BibleText%20section%22%3E%3Csection%3E%3Ch2%20class%3D%22bk_ch_vs_header%22%3E1%20Chronicles%2026%3A12-27%3A34%2C%20NLT%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_26_12%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2226%22%20vn%3D%2212%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-sp%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E12%3C%2Fspan%3EThese%20divisions%20of%20the%20gatekeepers%20were%20named%20for%20their%20family%20leaders%2C%20and%20like%20the%20other%20Levites%2C%20they%20served%20at%20the%20house%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_26_13%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2226%22%20vn%3D%2213%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E13%3C%2Fspan%3EThey%20were%20assigned%20by%20families%20for%20guard%20duty%20at%20the%20various%20gates%2C%20without%20regard%20to%20age%20or%20training%2C%20for%20it%20was%20all%20decided%20by%20means%20of%20sacred%20lots.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_26_14%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2226%22%20vn%3D%2214%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E14%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20responsibility%20for%20the%20east%20gate%20went%20to%20Meshelemiah%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E26%3A14%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3EShelemiah%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20a%20variant%20spelling%20of%20Meshelemiah%3B%20compare%2026%3A2.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20and%20his%20group.%20The%20north%20gate%20was%20assigned%20to%20his%20son%20Zechariah%2C%20a%20man%20of%20unusual%20wisdom.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_26_15%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2226%22%20vn%3D%2215%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E15%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20south%20gate%20went%20to%20Obed-edom%2C%20and%20his%20sons%20were%20put%20in%20charge%20of%20the%20storehouse.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_26_16%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2226%22%20vn%3D%2216%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E16%3C%2Fspan%3EShuppim%20and%20Hosah%20were%20assigned%20the%20west%20gate%20and%20the%20gateway%20leading%20up%20to%20the%20Temple.%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E26%3A16%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Or%20%3Cem%3Ethe%20gate%20of%20Shalleketh%20on%20the%20upper%20road%3C%2Fem%3E%20(also%20in%2026%3A18).%20The%20meaning%20of%20the%20Hebrew%20is%20uncertain.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Guard%20duties%20were%20divided%20evenly.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_26_17%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2226%22%20vn%3D%2217%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E17%3C%2Fspan%3ESix%20Levites%20were%20assigned%20each%20day%20to%20the%20east%20gate%2C%20four%20to%20the%20north%20gate%2C%20four%20to%20the%20south%20gate%2C%20and%20two%20pairs%20at%20the%20storehouse.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_26_18%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2226%22%20vn%3D%2218%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E18%3C%2Fspan%3ESix%20were%20assigned%20each%20day%20to%20the%20west%20gate%2C%20four%20to%20the%20gateway%20leading%20up%20to%20the%20Temple%2C%20and%20two%20to%20the%20courtyard.%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E26%3A18%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Or%20%3Cem%3Ethe%20colonnade.%3C%2Fem%3E%20The%20meaning%20of%20the%20Hebrew%20is%20uncertain.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_26_19%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2226%22%20vn%3D%2219%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E19%3C%2Fspan%3EThese%20were%20the%20divisions%20of%20the%20gatekeepers%20from%20the%20clans%20of%20Korah%20and%20Merari.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_26_20%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2226%22%20vn%3D%2220%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3ETreasurers%20and%20Other%20Officials%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E20%3C%2Fspan%3EOther%20Levites%2C%20led%20by%20Ahijah%2C%20were%20in%20charge%20of%20the%20treasuries%20of%20the%20house%20of%20God%20and%20the%20treasuries%20of%20the%20gifts%20dedicated%20to%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_26_21%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2226%22%20vn%3D%2221%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E21%3C%2Fspan%3EFrom%20the%20family%20of%20Libni%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E26%3A21a%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3ELadan%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20a%20variant%20spelling%20of%20Libni%3B%20compare%206%3A17.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20in%20the%20clan%20of%20Gershon%2C%20Jehiel%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E26%3A21b%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3EJehieli%3C%2Fem%3E%20(also%20in%2026%3A22)%2C%20a%20variant%20spelling%20of%20Jehiel%3B%20compare%2023%3A8.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20was%20the%20leader.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_26_22%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2226%22%20vn%3D%2222%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E22%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20sons%20of%20Jehiel%2C%20Zetham%20and%20his%20brother%20Joel%2C%20were%20in%20charge%20of%20the%20treasuries%20of%20the%20house%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_26_23%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2226%22%20vn%3D%2223%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E23%3C%2Fspan%3EThese%20are%20the%20leaders%20that%20descended%20from%20Amram%2C%20Izhar%2C%20Hebron%2C%20and%20Uzziel%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_26_24%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2226%22%20vn%3D%2224%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22ext-hanging-sp%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E24%3C%2Fspan%3EFrom%20the%20clan%20of%20Amram%2C%20Shebuel%20was%20a%20descendant%20of%20Gershom%20son%20of%20Moses.%20He%20was%20the%20chief%20officer%20of%20the%20treasuries.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_26_25%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2226%22%20vn%3D%2225%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E25%3C%2Fspan%3EHis%20relatives%20through%20Eliezer%20were%20Rehabiah%2C%20Jeshaiah%2C%20Joram%2C%20Zicri%2C%20and%20Shelomoth.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_26_26%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2226%22%20vn%3D%2226%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22ext-body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E26%3C%2Fspan%3EShelomoth%20and%20his%20relatives%20were%20in%20charge%20of%20the%20treasuries%20containing%20the%20gifts%20that%20King%20David%2C%20the%20family%20leaders%2C%20and%20the%20generals%20and%20captains%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E26%3A26%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3Ethe%20commanders%20of%20thousands%20and%20of%20hundreds.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20and%20other%20officers%20of%20the%20army%20had%20dedicated%20to%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_26_27%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2226%22%20vn%3D%2227%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E27%3C%2Fspan%3EThese%20men%20dedicated%20some%20of%20the%20plunder%20they%20had%20gained%20in%20battle%20to%20maintain%20the%20house%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_26_28%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2226%22%20vn%3D%2228%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E28%3C%2Fspan%3EShelomoth%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E26%3A28%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3EShelomith%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20a%20variant%20spelling%20of%20Shelomoth.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20and%20his%20relatives%20also%20cared%20for%20the%20gifts%20dedicated%20to%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20by%20Samuel%20the%20seer%2C%20Saul%20so